# Simple guide to set up and deploying your Website 2019 Update (RStudio - Git - GitHub - Netlify)

1. Open R Studio


### Create an project under your target folder (e.g Website)

devtools::install_github("rstudio/blogdown")
library(blogdown)
install_hugo()

Create a new folder Blog in Website folder
set your directory in R to the repo in Github ==> Blog
new_site()
or blogdown::new_site(theme = "gcushen/hugo-academic")
or
install_theme("gcushen/hugo-academic", theme_example = TRUE, update_config = TRUE)


### Uploading your local git repositroy to Github

BASH commands:
Choose the folder where your website will be
cd Website/BLOG
git init
git remote add origin https://github.com/korur/Website.git
git add .
git commit -m take
git push origin master

---
## **git pull**
If you change something on github page: go to your local .git repository and  
execute git pull origin master



on github create CNAME file with your domain name.


###Create netlify toml on your local repository

Netlify TOML
https://gohugo.io/hosting-and-deployment/hosting-on-netlify/
(works)  

# check your hugo version and update in the toml document
in Rstudio type blogdown::hugo_version()

+++Customization of Hugo Academic++++

go to content folder >> home 
choose widget >> e.g projects.md >> activate = true >> false


###Create a repository on Github

on the config.toml
add publishDir = "docs"
and github website address

